= Xivo install cd for wheezy XiVO five =

    apt-get install simple-cdd syslinux-common netpbm mtools dosfstools

cat /etc/apt/sources.list.d/xivo-for-cd-build.list

    deb http://mirror.xivo.io/debian/ xivo-dev main

generate CD with following command:

    simple-cdd --dist wheezy -g  --profiles-udeb-dist wheezy --conf ./xivo.conf

Docker
======

Min version: 1.7.0

To init the build with docker:

    ./init-docker.sh

To build CD with docker, first build the docker image.

For 32 bit.

    docker build -t xivo-cd32 -f dockerfile/32/Dockerfile .

For 64 bit.

    docker build -t xivo-cd64 -f dockerfile/64/Dockerfile .

Then run the 32 bit container:

    docker run -v /tmp/cd32/images:/home/builder/xivo-install-cd/images \
               -v /tmp/cd32:/home/builder/xivo-install-cd/tmp \
               -v /tmp/xivo_packages/:/tmp/xivo_packages/ \
               -it xivo-cd32 bash
    ./build-iso.sh

The iso result is on directory images or on /tmp/cd32/images on the host.

Docker compose
==============

Min version: 1.3.1

Then run:

    docker-compose up -d

Iso can be found on /tmp/cd$ARCH/images on the host.

ARCH is 32 or 64.
